# Project conventions (NestJS)

When creating or editing modules, controllers, services, repos, entities, or DTOs in this project, always follow the rules defined in **.cursor/instructions.md**.

In summary:
- **Architecture:** Controller → Service → Repo → Database. Controller forwards to service; service calls repo only; repo contains all DB logic (QueryBuilder, no raw SQL).
- **Response format:** `{ status, messageEn, messageAr, data, meta? }` for all API responses.
- **DTOs:** CreateDto, UpdateDto, PaginationDto, SearchDto; use class-validator and @ApiProperty.
- **Controller:** Swagger on every endpoint; CRUD + GET /search + PUT /:id/toggle-status; use PaginationDto and SearchDto.
- **Repo:** Extend Repository<Entity>; implement createEntity, findAll, findById, search, updateEntity, deleteEntity, toggleStatus; return structured { status, messageEn, messageAr, data, meta }.
- **Entity:** TypeORM naming, relations, audit fields (created_date, updated_date) where applicable.
- **Pagination:** skip, take, status, area_id (if applicable). Search: search, status, area_id, email/phone if applicable.

Refer to .cursor/instructions.md and .cursor/templates/ for exact patterns and templates.
